<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 04 at 5:19PM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>A band of snow, heavy at times, is moving through Southwest
Montana, reducing visibility to 1/4 mile at times. Heavy snow may
occur across I-90 between Homestake Pass and Bozeman Pass, where
snow rates can approach 1 inch per hour. Those traveling in these
areas are urged to drive slow with low beams on, keeping the
distance between you and the driver in front of you.</description>
